      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Paul Verhelst</b>\n</p><p><b>Paul Verhelst</b>,<br />\na Dutch computer chess expert, who published and maintained interesting chess <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and <a href=\"/Programming\" title=\"Programming\">chess programming</a> sites <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>.\n<a href=\"/Ed_Schroder\" title=\"Ed Schroder\">Ed Schröder</a> once mentioned the <a href=\"/0x88\" title=\"0x88\">0x88</a> <a href=\"/0x88#SquareRelations\" title=\"0x88\">square difference</a> lookup as Paul Verhelst way <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, which was used and described by <a href=\"/Paul_Wiereyn\" title=\"Paul Wiereyn\">Paul Wiereyn</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and, according to <a href=\"/David_Kittinger\" title=\"David Kittinger\">David Kittinger</a>, was originally attributed to <a href=\"/Mikhail_Botvinnik\" title=\"Mikhail Botvinnik\">Mikhail Botvinnik</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paul_Verhelst&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=59315&amp;start=11\">Re: futility pruning</a> by <a href=\"/Ed_Schroder\" title=\"Ed Schroder\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 11, 2016&#160;» <a href=\"/Futility_Pruning\" title=\"Futility Pruning\">Futility Pruning</a>, <a href=\"/Vector_Attacks\" title=\"Vector Attacks\">Vector Attacks</a>, <a href=\"/0x88\" title=\"0x88\">0x88</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paul_Verhelst&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://verhelst.org/\">Het Familieklokje | Web pagina’s van de familie Verhelst uit Tilburg</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://verhelst.org/chess/\">Computer Chess Programming</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20010406054224/http://www.xs4all.nl/~verhelst/\">Paul Verhelst's homepage</a> (<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wayback_Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>, April 07, 2001)</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20010405091155/http://www.xs4all.nl/~verhelst/chess/programming.html\">Paul Verhelst's chess programming pages</a> (<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wayback_Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>, April 05, 2001)</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paul_Verhelst&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20010408203313/http://www.xs4all.nl/~verhelst/chess/links.html\">Paul Verhelst's chess pages</a> (<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wayback_Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>, April 08, 2001)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20010405091155/http://www.xs4all.nl/~verhelst/chess/programming.html\">Paul Verhelst's chess programming pages</a> (<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wayback_Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>, April 05, 2001)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=59315&amp;start=11\">Re: futility pruning</a> by <a href=\"/Ed_Schroder\" title=\"Ed Schroder\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 11, 2016</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Paul_Wiereyn\" title=\"Paul Wiereyn\">Paul Wiereyn</a> (<b>1985</b>). <i>Inventive Problem Solving</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#8_4\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 8, No. 4</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=462693&amp;t=43447\">Re: Hello all</a> by <a href=\"/David_Kittinger\" title=\"David Kittinger\">Dave Kittinger</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 26, 2012</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301051636\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.008 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.009 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 85/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 194/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:7700-0!canonical and timestamp 20260301051636 and revision id 23591\n -->\n"
